{
  "texts": [
    "GCN employs the following function to compute node embeddings (Welling and Kipf 2016):",
    "Fig. 3 The general scheme of a graph neural network.",
    "Left: a graph (with the neighbourhood of node a).",
    "Right: the embedding generated for node a using a 3-layer GNN.",
    "Each rhombus presents a function that consists of a linear transformation, an aggregation function (sum, mean etc), and an activation function (ReLU, sigmoid etc) (Chehreghani 2022) where W is a trainable matrix, is a nonlinear function and N(v) is the set of neighbors of v."
  ]
}